    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You're going to need to update your compile SDK to 31. It <em>sounds</em> like it's currently set to 30. In your Gradle files there should be something like <code>compileSdk</code> in the <code>android</code> block.</p>\n<p>Bump that up to 31. If that's an issue for some reason, you can also bump down your dependencies to versions that don't require that compile SDK version.</p>\n"
